line_1: Let me, whose humbler muse hath ne'er aspir'd
line_2: By elegiac song be now inspir'd,

line_1: I only to the Fight aspir'd:
line_2: Was all the Glory I desir'd.

line_1: No more the birds to charm the year aspir'd,
line_2: And wand'ring lovers from the plain retir'd;

line_1: Not he to th'Crown, the Crown to him aspir'd;
line_2: The rising Stem with thirst of Glory fir'd,

line_1: He saw, he wish'd, and to the Prize aspir'd:
line_2: Th' Adventrous Baron the bright Locks admir'd,

line_1: Without a Crime my Passion had aspir'd,
line_2: Found the lov'd Prince, and told what I desir'd.
